SIMPLE: suffocate
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Suffocate
<hw>Suf"fo*cate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>suffocatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>suffocare</ets> to choke;
<ets>sub</ets> under + <ets>fauces</ets> the throat. Cf.
<er>Faucal</er>.]</ety> <def>Suffocated; choked.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suffocate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Suffocate
<hw>Suf"fo*cate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Suffocated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Suffocating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To choke
or kill by stopping respiration; to stifle; to smother.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let not hemp his windpipe <qex>suffocate</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To destroy; to extinguish; <as>as, to
<ex>suffocate</ex> fire</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suffocate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Suffocate
<hw>Suf"fo*cate</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To become choked, stifled,
or smothered.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A swelling discontent is apt to
<xex>suffocate</xex> and strangle without passage.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>collier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suffocating</ent>⟦br⟧
